# Cursor Rules — Lithium Prospectivity Pilot Pipeline (MVP)

## Read first
Before any work, read docs/00_PROJECT_BRIEF.md, docs/01_ARCHITECTURE.md,
docs/02_BUILD_PLAN.md, docs/03_CODING_STANDARDS.md, docs/04_ACCEPTANCE_TESTS.md.
Follow them. They override default assumptions.

## Scope discipline
- This is an internally-run command-line pilot pipeline. It is NOT a web app.
- NEVER add, scaffold, or stub: web server, REST API, frontend, database,
  authentication, billing, customer-data upload, model training/retraining,
  or consent logic. If a task seems to need any of these, STOP and say so —
  the task is mis-scoped, not an invitation to add them.
- Do exactly ONE task from docs/02_BUILD_PLAN.md per session. Do not start a
  task whose predecessors are not complete and tested.

## The model and grid are frozen inputs
- models/model.pkl, models/feature_cols.json, models/label_encoder.pkl, and
  data/grid/features_v2.gpkg are PROVIDED. Load them; never train, modify, or
  regenerate them.
- Never change the model service interface (the predict() signature and the
  expected feature column contract) without explicit instruction in the chat.

## Engineering rules
- Write or confirm the acceptance test BEFORE implementing. Implement the
  smallest change that passes. Run the full test suite. Then stop.
- Determinism only: no unseeded randomness anywhere. Seed comes from config.py.
- All paths come from config.py. No hard-coded paths elsewhere.
- Pin every dependency with ==. Do not add a dependency without stating why.
- Fail loudly and specifically: every error names the file, value, or column
  at fault. Never swallow exceptions.
- No global mutable state. One responsibility per module. Modules never reach
  backward in the data flow defined in 01_ARCHITECTURE.md.

## Output discipline
- Do not make changes outside the scope of the current task.
- Do not "helpfully" refactor unrelated code. If you see an unrelated problem,
  report it; do not fix it in this task's diff.
- Keep diffs small enough to review in ~10 minutes. If a task needs a larger
  diff, it is mis-scoped — say so instead of proceeding.

## Verbatim text
- Use the methodology and limitations text from docs/03_CODING_STANDARDS.md
  exactly. Do not paraphrase reviewed wording.

## When unsure
Stop and ask. A wrong assumption acted on confidently is the most expensive
failure mode here. A clarifying question is always cheaper.
